programme.desc: The Sûreté du Québec counts on a group of elite rescuers to intervene in dangerous situations. Meet the Tactical Intervention Group, made up of the best policemen in the province, who are specifically recruited for their physical and mental abilities.

programme.title: Divorce Court: The Punisher
programme.desc: Shea says Jessica constantly punishes him due her history of cheating exes. She must know where Shea is every second forcing his friends to cut ties. Jessica has caught Shea lying to her in the past. Can Judge Lynn Toler get them on track?

programme.title: Divorce Court: Sick and Tired
programme.desc: Timothy is tired of being kicked out the house every time Erin catches an attitude. If she kicks him out once more, he's gone for good. Erin says she dropped out of college and left behind a full tennis scholarship because of him.

programme.title: Divorce Court: Irreplaceable
programme.desc: Quanasia can no longer deal with Chandler's lying just so he can have his affairs. Chandler says she lost her drive after having his kids. Can Judge Toler wake her up from Chandler's hypnotizing charm or is this couple a lost cause?

programme.title: Divorce Court: Drank Sinatra
programme.desc: Kayla's excessive drinking along with the cheating is a deal breaker from Bryan. Bryan can no longer tolerate Kayla's alcohol-fueled tantrums. She says he is controlling and doesn't put her and her child first. Can Judge Toler save this couple?

programme.title: Divorce Court: Age Ain't Nothin but a Number
programme.desc: Kelley feels Keionte's childish behavior has her considering burning their marriage license. He claims that once they married, Mommie Dearest was born and no longer wants to be her business partner! Can they figure it out before it's too late?
programme.sub-title: Age Ain't Nothin but a Number

programme.title: Divorce Court: Enough Is Enough
programme.desc: Dwight has had it with Roxy's mental abuse. Dwight says Roxy has cost him multiple jobs because she's constantly harassing him at work, but she says he needs to give her the attention she deserves! Can Judge Toler help them see eye to eye?

programme.title: Divorce Court: Old Town Road
programme.desc: Jennifer says Josh's lies have left her and their family homeless. He has made many hurtful decisions like selling her car and dumping her dog while she was giving birth to their son. Can he pave the way for a future?

programme.title: Divorce Court: Once a Cheater Always a Cheater

programme.sub-title: Once a Cheater Always a Cheater

programme.title: Divorce Court: Love on Top

programme.title: Divorce Court: Alpha Girl

programme.title: Divorce Court: The Ex
programme.desc: Andwela and Nicole came together after cheating on their spouses. Nicole feels like their marriage has been severely damaged due to his disloyalty and him trash talking her to his ex. Can this couple figure it out?

programme.title: Divorce Court: Forever My Lady
programme.desc: Despite their age gap, Tamara and Jasimine have been together for 10 years. Tamara claims Jasimine sends risque texts to other people. Jasimine claims Tamara explodes in fits of rage. Can this couple get over their age gap?

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Ladder

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Firehouse

programme.title: Paranormal State: Hide and Seek

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Name
programme.desc: Ryan Buell and company set out on one of their most dangerous cases to date - to help a single mother who is experiencing paranormal activity in a home that was once the site of brutal murder.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dark Practice
programme.desc: Brenda is terrified by a dark hooded figure spotted in her West Virginia home. The same entity allegedly tormented her late husband. PRS and Psychic/Medium Michelle Belanger help Brenda before she slips into the same abyss as her late husband.

programme.title: Paranormal State: If I Should Die...

programme.title: Paranormal State: Vendetta
programme.desc: P.R.S. investigates claims of supernatural revenge in the Pennsylvania Poconos. When a client's new boyfriend moves in, does the paranormal move in with him? Or did her ex put a hex on her house and the entire family?

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Special Love - Part 1
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark persuade a youngster with Down's Syndrome to join the Special Olympics.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Special Love - Part 2

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: For the Love of Larry

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Another Kind of War, Another Kind of Peace

programme.sub-title: Another Kind of War, Another Kind of Peace

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Clare Moore
programme.desc: A lifetime of neglect has left Clare Moore with no confidence and even less style. With hand-me-down clothes and a home-style hair-cut, Clare's paranoid about her appearance and she should be. Fiona McDonald and her team of experts come to the rescue.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Serving Up Style
programme.desc: Michelle's a diner waitress whose looks need to be sent back. So our doctors will restore her skin and smile. Then the Glam Squad will serve up some style, update her hair and give her makeup tips. In the end, Michelle will look 10 YEARS YOUNGER.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Picture Perfect
programme.desc: Stacey is a homemaker who aspires to a career in photography but is embarrassed to show her own face. After a makeover in the glam capitol, Beverly Hills, will Stacey be picture perfect?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Ruth Reddy
programme.desc: Ruth Reddy's look is camped in the 80's - big hair, big shoulder pads, and big problems. So it's up to Fiona McDonald to reunite her with the world of fashion, making her look 10 years younger in just 10 days.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Youth Motivator
programme.desc: After years of turmoil, Naomi has turned her life around by mentoring youth. Now that she's found her calling, she wants to regain a vibrant appearance to better relate. Can we help her in her quest by making her look TEN YEARS YOUNGER?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back To Glamour
programme.desc: Rebecca gets a sophisticated makeover to bring back some of the glamour from her pre-mom days. Now, her husband can recognize the girl he married, but will she look 10 Years Younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Geek To Chic
programme.desc: Susan is a married mom and a successful chemist. But she's afraid her appearance hurts her professional image. We're going to help Susan shake that geeky scientist image and make her look 10 YEARS YOUNGER.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sue Chamberlain
programme.desc: For the past 12 years Sue Chamberlain has been harbouring a devastating secret. She's entirely lost her confidence and her youth. Presenter Nicky Hambleton-Jones and a team of experts revive Sue's confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Different Strokes
programme.desc: Zuri is a hard working single mother of two with no time or energy for herself. In a relationship with a man her own age who looks younger, she is embarrassed to be mistaken for his mother. The Glam Squad does their magic to roll back the years.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Beauty is More Than Skin Deep
programme.desc: Tracy is a dedicated single mom, and a survivor. After devastating cystic acne scarred her face, she suffered a terrible oven accident that left her with even more scars. Our team of experts, and The Glam Squad, give Tracy the TLC she deserves
programme.sub-title: Beauty is More Than Skin Deep

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Tania Hammond
programme.desc: In an ideal world, Tania Hammond would like to be pop star Mariah Carey, but her flaming red hair, milk bottle glasses and teeth that arrive half and hour before her face scream rock bottom not rock chick.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Prepping For The Big Day
programme.desc: Lilia is the first in her family to finish college. She helps support her family and bought a house she shares with her mother. Her achievements have carried a price; she looks old and tired compared to her friends.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Saying "I Do" To A New Look
programme.desc: Maggie, a sassy gal from Scotland, is about to marry a man 13 years younger then her! This mother of two has found love, but doesn't want to look like she is the mom giving the groom away when she walks down the aisle. Our team is up for the challenge.
programme.sub-title: Saying "I Do" To A New Look

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Richard Power "One Year On"
programme.desc: Last year, 35 year old Richard Power was living life to the limits – and it showed. A year later, we recap Richard's rocky relationship with our femme fatale of flair – and see whether a catch-up with Nicky will set things straight.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Age is No Laughing Matter
programme.desc: Years ago, Bobby was a rising star in the world of stand-up comedy. With thinning hair and a less than desirable wardrobe, Bobby's convinced his looks are no laughing matter. It's time for The Glam Squad and their experts to put Bobby back on stage.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny is throwing himself into his work after the death of his father, and has applied for the role of State Vet. However, Danny's attempts to involve Thabo in the first phase of the Lion Breeding Project lead to Du Plessis feeling like an outsider.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: It is Danny's first day as State Vet and when he helps rescue some smuggled animals he feels he's making a difference. However, he discovers the role isn't going to be all plain sailing.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny's first big project as State Vet is a major animal translocation, and he is desperate to impress. Meanwhile, whilst Alice is out in the bush treating an injured zebra, she is stalked by lions. She makes it back to her jeep in time but is shaken up.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Alice is still suffering from a loss of nerve after her close shave with the lions and so Danny tries to help her overcome her problems – the Leopard's Den lions have produced their first cub and he needs Alice back in the saddle.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: In his role as State Vet, Danny works with wealthy conservationist, Anton Ziegler, to catch a group of leopard hunters. Ziegler is also buying a tiger from Vanessa, who struggling with her finances, desperately needs the money to ensure Mara's future.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Du Plessis has started a one man campaign of vandalism against the new neighbours at Mara; Peeters and the mining company. When Peeters catches him on CCTV, Du Plessis is fined and given a restraining order to keep him away from Mara.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Du Plessis comes to meet Caroline's plane but he doesn't seem happy – he has seen that the mining company have already started building the road which threatens Leopard's Den.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: The family are making arrangements to leave Leopard's Den, all except Du Plessis who is steadfastly refusing to accept that he has lost his home. He won't use his share of the money from the sale of the land to buy somewhere else.

programme.title: House of Tiny Tearaways: Episode 36

programme.title: House of Tiny Tearaways: Episode 4

programme.title: Tattoo Fixers: Episode 4

programme.title: Supercars: Porsche to the Max!

programme.title: Motorcycles: Stereotypes on Two Wheels

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coasts
programme.desc: Along coasts, one element ends and another begins. No two days are ever the same on a coastline: the only thing that remains a constant is the timeless power of the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Lost Cities
programme.desc: Once powerful and populous centers of influence, these lost cities are providing clues to how our ancestors existed in the world and remind us that ancient civilizations were not so far removed from our own.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Timeless Cities & Towns
programme.desc: These cities and towns are special places where the past coexists with the present, creating cultures totally unique to their people and their part of the world and adhering to ancient traditions and while introducing modern innovations.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Iconic Buildings
programme.desc: In construction, only a few buildings can be groundbreaking. Vastly different in shape, size, and function, these diverse buildings prove there is no recipe for greatness, just the fundamental ingredients of vision, bravery, and imagination.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Bridges
programme.desc: A bridge is a structure that’s designed to transcend, but a great bridge can define the place where it stands. Symbols of human ingenuity, beauty, and grandeur, bridges connect us not only to each other but also to the past.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Monuments & Landmarks
programme.desc: Many of the world’s most significant manmade wonders serve not as dwellings, but as powerful signposts. But more than giving us direction, they tell us a story - they characterize powerful forces, or commemorate power lost.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Sacred Sites
programme.desc: Ancient in architecture and detailed in design, these man-made masterpieces stand as testaments to the strength of human faith. These sites endure as a timeless reminder of resilience, respect, and the need to reflect.

programme.title: Arthur: Prunella's Special Edition/The Secret Life Of Dogs & Babies

programme.sub-title: Prunella's Special Edition/The Secret Life Of Dogs & Babies

programme.sub-title: The Boy Who Cried Comet/Arthur and Los Vecinos

programme.sub-title: Rhyme For Your Life/For Whom The Bell Tolls

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Settle the Score

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: The Line Goes Dead

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Murder Bites

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Bubba & Garrett

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cesar and the Horse Whisperer (Chloe & Hobo, Ali)

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Boo and Britney Dawg

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Hank & Paris
programme.desc: Marsha Alexander’s rescued Mastiff has ruined the furniture and intimidates anyone walking by his gate. Paris, a long hair Chihuahua, looks fashionable, but barks and snaps at strangers.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Duke & Lulu, and Sparky
programme.desc: Cesar heads to the dog park to help some frustrated dog lovers. A therapeutic terrier helps AJ control her panic attacks but tends to attack other dogs.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Jake in Exile
programme.desc: An Australian Shepherd/Pit Bull Mix has severe aggression problems towards women. A Boxer is an expert escape artist, able to jump the 6 foot backyard fence. Her owners are concerned for her safety.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cesar's Worst Bite
programme.desc: Holly, a Labrador puppy, displays severe food aggression; a women's shelter will take a needy woman and her pit bull, Tucker, but Cesar must help the dog become less protective first.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Widow’s Dogs, Drool Dog, Dexter Follow-up
programme.desc: A retriever mix, and wire hair fox terriers siblings, have turned into a combative pack. A Sharpei/Dobie mix drools excessively. Rottie mix Dexter travels to Los Angeles for a refresher course.
programme.sub-title: Widow’s Dogs, Drool Dog, Dexter Follow-up

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Mouse Mania_Wigged Out

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: This Little Piggy_All Dolled Up

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: My Strange Addiction Special 1

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: In Love With Balloons/Face Mask Eater

programme.sub-title: In Love With Balloons/Face Mask Eater

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Blood Drinker

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Loves Baby Wipes/Eats Sand
programme.desc: Riah has been addicted to baby wipes since she was 15 and goes through up to 500 every day. Brea has been addicted to eating sand for the past 5 years.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Grown-Up Baby

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Star Chaser_The Little Merman
programme.desc: Eric is obsessed with Mermaids and has transformed himself into a real-life Merman. Vanessa is so obsessed with meeting celebrities that she spends all day searching them out.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Married to a Doll/Picking My Scabs

programme.sub-title: Married to a Doll/Picking My Scabs

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Greg Dreams of Jeannie_The Amazing Squirrel

programme.sub-title: Greg Dreams of Jeannie_The Amazing Squirrel

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: 5,000 Kids_Tickled Pink

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Airline Addict_Crazy for Capybaras

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Ketchup_Mustard

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Fish Out Of Water
programme.desc: Grant and Khrissy just got engaged. He’s all-Alaskan but she’s a fish out of water from the Deep South. The couple wants to buy a house that’s a mix of the Alaskan bush and her Alabama roots.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Outhouse Life
programme.desc: Sean and Charlotte want a home in Fairbanks, Alaska, that won’t cost them a penny in utility bills. So they’re going off-the-grid. And that means one thing… there’ll be no bathrooms.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Hangar Homes
programme.desc: Born and bred Alaskans Andy and Nicole grew up in a town so remote, their family vehicles were airplanes! Now that they’re looking for a new home, they need an airplane hangar and a runway.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Remote Coves
programme.desc: Charlie and Toni are outdoor adventure junkies who want a home in Alaska that’s so remote they can catch their next meal from the ocean right off their front porch.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Homer Bound
programme.desc: Nathan and Lindsay are brand new to Alaska. They want a house similar to where Nathan’s pioneer grandfather lived, in the bayside town of Homer, surrounded by the great outdoors.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Life On A Mountain
programme.desc: Russ and Dana search for a home in the town of Girdwood, Alaska, at the base of towering Mount Alyeska. The views are spectacular, but the danger of an avalanches is real.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Guys Getaway
programme.desc: David Parks and Chris Erickson are best friends, and professional handymen. They want to buy a weekend getaway house in the wilds of Alaska, but they don’t want to spend a lot of money.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Juneau Waterfront
programme.desc: Chris and Heidi are marine adventurers who want Alaska’s marine wildlife right out their front door. They want to buy a home on the coveted waterfront of the oceanside city of Juneau.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Tiny Homes, Big Mountain

programme.title: World's Greatest: Sacred Sites
programme.desc: Ancient in architecture and detailed in design, these man-made masterpieces stand as testaments to the strength of human faith. These sites endure as a timeless reminder of resilience, respect, and the need to reflect.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Treks
programme.desc: Every journey made by foot promises a grand adventure. From the highest mountains to the wildest jungle realms, treks venture down the road less travelled, allowing us to connect to nature, history, and culture, one step at a time.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Cruises
programme.desc: There is something seductive about setting sail. Cruises offer us a chance to dip our toes into the 70% of our planet awash with oceans, rivers, and lakes, exploring places that can only be reached by daring to leave the shore.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Water Adventures
programme.desc: We are captivated by oceans, rivers, and lakes - the power, the flow, the reflective stillness. And as we seek to get closer, we immerse ourselves in an expanding range of aquatic experiences.

programme.title: Arthur: Elwood City Turns 100!

programme.title: Arthur: Pick a Car, Any Car/Jenna's Bedtime Blues
programme.desc: The family car is broken, and so is Arthur's heart. How can Mom and Dad even think of replacing it? It’s Muffy's annual slumber party, and Jenna is finally invited! But what if the other girls discover that she's an occasional bed-wetter?
programme.sub-title: Pick a Car, Any Car/Jenna's Bedtime Blues

programme.title: Arthur: The World of Tomorrow/Is There a Doctor in the House?
programme.desc: Since Binky's repeating third grade, he's totally dreading Mr. Ratburn's annual class sleepover at the Science Museum. Arthur and D.W. face the ultimate challenge when Mom gets a bad cold and then gives it to Dad!
programme.sub-title: The World of Tomorrow/Is There a Doctor in the House?

programme.title: Arthur: Prunella Sees the Light/Return of the Snowball

programme.sub-title: Prunella Sees the Light/Return of the Snowball

programme.title: Arthur: April 9th
programme.desc: April 9th is a normal day until a fire destroys the teacher's lounge and forces Lakewood Elementary to close. This unexpected event finds creates a wide range of emotional reactions, for Arthur, his friends and teachers, and the community.

programme.title: Arthur: Dear Adil/Bitzi's Break-Up
programme.desc: Arthur is worried that his letters to his new Turkish pen pal, Adil, will be boring. After all, how can Elwood City compare to Arthur's fantastical ideas about Turkey? Bitzi is breaking up with her boyfriend, and Buster is really sad.

programme.title: Arthur: Arthur's Snow Biz/Bugged
programme.desc: Winter hits Elwood City and Arthur sees dollar signs! His snow-shoveling business is booming--that is, until Buster decides to get in on the action. And, Brain can be a know-it-all, and sometimes he really bugs people.

programme.title: Arthur: Fernkenstein's Monster/D.W., Dancing Queen
programme.desc: Inspired by Mary Shelley's "Frankenstein," Fern tells a tale so scary that Arthur and the gang become afraid of her! Then, Binky decides to teach D.W. to dance, but she just doesn't seem to get the moves. Is D.W. a no-talent klutz?

programme.title: Arthur: Vomitrocious!/Sue Ellen Chickens Out
programme.desc: It's just a regular day until Francine starts to feel queasy, and then throws up in the cafeteria! Now Francine is afraid to go back to school. And, Sue Ellen learns that a fast-food chain is taking over the beloved Sugar Bowl.

programme.title: Arthur: Postcards from Buster, Parts I & II
programme.desc: Buster's going to New York City to meet his dad Bo, and the Reads are coming with him! He's thrilled ... but won't his mom miss him? But, Bitzi gives him a present that will let him share his exciting trip with her--a video camera!
programme.sub-title: Postcards from Buster, Parts I & II

programme.title: Arthur: Desk Wars/Desperately Seeking Stanley
programme.desc: When Mr. Ratburn moves Brain and Arthur away from their usual desks, it sets off a chain reaction resulting in the most explosive desk war in third grade history! And, Arthur is 8-years old now—does he still need his teddy bear?

programme.title: Arthur: Muffy's Art Attack/Tales from the Crib
programme.desc: When Muffy sees a kinetic sculptor’s machines, she brags that she can make even better ones. Then, Vicita is upset at having to trade in her cherished crib for a big-girl bed, so D.W. shares her story of that same rite of passage.
programme.sub-title: Muffy's Art Attack/Tales from the Crib

programme.title: Catfish: The TV Show Daytime: Jarrod & Abby
programme.desc: How do young people who've embraced the digital age find love? Often by connecting online with others they've never met in person before. The problem -- that cute guy you may be falling in love with could be lying about who he really is.

programme.title: Catfish: The TV Show Daytime: Kya & Alyx
programme.desc: In this episode we meet Kya and Alyx, who fell in love quickly after meeting online. Are they being honest with each other? Hosts Nev Schulman and Max Joseph investigate.

programme.title: Catfish: The TV Show Daytime: Joe & Kari Ann
programme.desc: Joe was sceptical when Miss Teen USA, Kari, sent him a friend request. Now, after months of communication, Joe thinks it might be the real deal, and he might have found love with her.

programme.title: Catfish: The TV Show Daytime: Tyler & Amanda
programme.desc: After a year and a half of chatting with her online, Tyler thinks he may have a future with Amanda. But are Tyler's friends correct because they suspect that something isn't right?

programme.title: Catfish: The TV Show Daytime: Rod & Ebony
programme.desc: Rod met Ebony on a dating web site four years ago, now it's time for the two to meet in person. Is Ebony who she says she is? What will happen when they meet in real life for the first time?

programme.title: Catfish: The TV Show Daytime: Stephanie & David
programme.desc: Catfish brings together couples who've interacted solely through screens. In this edition, Stephanie searches for the man she's been talking to in an unseen episode.

programme.title: Catfish: The TV Show Daytime: Rico & Ja'Mari
programme.desc: Rico wants to move to England to care for his ailing mother, but his intense online relationship with Ja'mari, an international male model, is giving him second thoughts about leaving.

programme.title: Catfish: The TV Show Daytime: Mike & Felicia
programme.desc: Mike and Felicia met online and soon hit it off. After agreeing to meet, Felicia stood Mike up, offering only thin excuses. Can Mike trust Felicia - or will he end up disappointed?

programme.title: 48 Hours

programme.title: Teen Mom 2: We Belong Together
programme.desc: Kailyn and Javi finally celebrate their wedding. Chelsea graduates and lands a job. Jenelle accepts a plea that puts her on supervised probation. Jeremy declines a local job. (S5, ep10)

programme.title: Teen Mom 2: Out of the Blue
programme.desc: Javi takes Isaac to Jo's for the first time. Adam responds to Chelsea's visitation objection. Ali tests out her wheelchair while Leah continues to struggle with Jeremy being away. (S5, ep11)

programme.title: Teen Mom 2: What You See is Not What You Get
programme.desc: Kailyn's baby is born. Chelsea struggles with the new visitation agreement. Leah and Jeremy work on their relationship. Jenelle is pregnant but things are on edge after Nathan's DUI arrest. (S5, ep12)
programme.sub-title: What You See is Not What You Get

programme.title: Teen Mom 2: That's the Way Love Goes
programme.desc: Javi goes back to work. Jo moves to a new apartment. Jenelle worries as things with Nathan worsen. Chelsea hears major news about Adam. Leah discovers the cause of Ali's muscular dystrophy. (S5, ep13)

programme.title: Teen Mom 2: Keep It Together
programme.desc: Javi goes back to work, leaving Kailyn alone. Jo moves. Jenelle and Nathan get worse. Chelsea hears some major news about Adam. Leah discovers the cause of Ali's muscular dystrophy. (S5, ep14)

programme.title: Teen Mom 2: When Everything Seems Wrong
programme.desc: Jenelle and Nathan cope with his upcoming jail time. Chelsea moves into her new home. Kailyn invites Jo and Vee to Isaac's birthday party. Leah struggles to balance work and family life. (S5, ep15)

programme.title: Teen Mom 2: Overload
programme.desc: Leah starts medication for her anxiety. Kailyn and Javi visit Joe and Vee's apartment. Nathan prepares for jail and Jenelle worries about being alone. Chelsea meets with a lawyer. (S5, ep16)

programme.title: Teen Mom 2: Harder Than It Looks
programme.desc: Jenelle struggles alone with Jace while Nathan is away. Leah and Jeremy clash over finances. Chelsea investigates Adam's legal charges from his accident. Kailyn celebrates her birthday. (S5, ep17)

programme.title: 16 & Pregnant: Reunion
programme.desc: Dr. Drew hosts an emotional finale as the teen mothers from the latest series share a stage, coming together with their boyfriends & parents to talk about the issues they face.

programme.title: 16 & Pregnant: Jordan
programme.desc: Jordan and her sister were models and best friends until Jordan's pregnancy put all that on hold. Now her boyfriend and her sister are competing to be her number one.

programme.title: 16 & Pregnant: Jennifer
programme.desc: After abandoning sports and losing her friends, Jennifer has to battle with her over-protective parents to accept her boyfriend before she gives birth to twin boys.

programme.title: 16 & Pregnant: Jamie
programme.desc: Raised by a single mum, Jamie is a straight A student with big plans for the future. But after getting pregnant she struggles to mould her immature boyfriend into the father she never had.

programme.title: 16 & Pregnant: Danielle
programme.desc: After following her mum's footsteps by becoming a teen mum, Danielle strives to prove she can do things differently. But she soon learns she needs help managing school, a job and a baby.

programme.title: 16 & Pregnant: Cleondra
programme.desc: Regarded as the most likely to succeed in her family, Cleondra shocks everyone by getting pregnant so young. Now she faces the tough decision to leave home and move in with her boyfriend.

programme.title: 16 & Pregnant: Kayla
programme.desc: Kayla's anorexia comes back full-force when she is pregnant. While struggling to put looks aside, Kayla realizes that the person she has always relied on, her mother, refuses to support her.

programme.title: 16 & Pregnant: Izabella
programme.desc: After hiding her pregnancy for eight months, Izabella is forced to reconsider who her true friends are. She then risks her family ties when her boyfriend betrays their trust.

programme.title: CSI: New York: Rain
programme.desc: A Chinatown robbery goes south when one security guard is killed and the other mistakenly fires shots at a gas tank, burning two of the robbers alive.

programme.title: CSI: New York: Three Generations Are Enough
programme.desc: Panic ensues at the New York Mercantile Exchange when a briefcase is left behind, it is traced back to a stockbroker who mysteriously disappeared.

programme.title: CSI: New York: Officer Blue
programme.desc: When a mounted New York City police officer is shot off his horse, Detective Mac Taylor and the team comb the city for suspects.

programme.title: CSI: New York: Tri-Borough
programme.desc: The electrocution of a young man on the third rail of the subway leads into the world of an extreme sport where taking risks is part of the game.

programme.title: CSI: New York: Recycling
programme.desc: Competitive dog owners become the prime suspects in a murder investigation when Detective Mac Taylor examines the death of a dog trainer.

programme.title: CSI: New York: Tanglewood
programme.desc: The investigation of a suburban kid found beaten to death in Van Cortland Park leads the CSI team to Tanglewood, home to a group of wannabe gangsters.

programme.title: CSI: New York: Blood, Sweat and Tears
programme.desc: Detectives Mac Taylor and Stella Bonasera uncover the body of a teenaged boy crammed into a 2’ x 2’ x 2’ box buried in the sand at Coney Island.

programme.title: CSI: New York: Love Run Cold
programme.desc: CSI: NY follows a group of investigators who work for the New York City crime lab. The series mixes gritty subject matter and deduction and places a great deal of emphasis on criminal profiling. The team is led by Detective Mac Taylor.

programme.title: CSI: Miami: Kill Zone
programme.desc: Three people are shot and killed in downtown Miami during rush hour and Horatio and the team must catch the killer fast.

programme.title: CSI: Miami: A Horrible Mind
programme.desc: A professor from a local university is found hanging from a tree after being tortured, she had been tortured for at least 4 hours before the hanging.

programme.title: CSI: Miami: Entrance Wound
programme.desc: Horatio and the team are called to investigate when a prostitute is found stabbed to death and stuffed under a bed after the body was cleaned.

programme.title: CSI: Miami: Bunk
programme.desc: When it's revealed that a ring of underground labs are manufacturing deadly drugs, Horatio and Speedle investigate the situation.

programme.title: CSI: Miami: Forced Entry
programme.desc: Horatio and Speedle investigate when a burglar and rapist has been sexually assaulted and taped to his bedposts after being suffocated to death.

programme.title: CSI: Miami: Evidence Of Things Unseen
programme.desc: Horatio and the team are called to investigate the murder of an eastern European immigrant stabbed to death in a peep show booth.

programme.title: CSI: Miami: Golden Parachute
programme.desc: CSI: MIAMI follows a South Florida team of forensic investigators who use both cutting-edge scientific methods and old-fashioned police work to solve crimes.

programme.title: CSI: Miami: Wet Foot, Dry Foot
programme.desc: After fishermen catch a tiger shark and discover a partial human torso in its stomach, evidence leads the team to suspect murder.

programme.title: Sins & Secrets: Oakland
programme.desc: In 2007, in Oakland, California, journalist Chauncey Bailey was gunned down in broad daylight by a masked man. But evidence soon surfaced that indicated this was no ordinary crime.

programme.title: Sins & Secrets: San Antonio
programme.desc: In 2009, in San Antonio, TX, beautiful Dana Clair Edwards, was found murdered in her condo. Evidence soon surfaced that suggested this wasn’t a random crime.

programme.title: Sins & Secrets: Athens
programme.desc: In 2009, well-heeled humanitarian Grady Nichols seemed like the most revered man in all of Athens. Until he was shot on his back porch in an apparent botched robbery.

programme.title: Sins & Secrets: St. Michaels
programme.desc: On Valentine’s Day 1998, a stunned woman approached the front desk of a St Michaels, Maryland resort to report a fire in her hotel room where a charred body was pulled from the smoke.

programme.title: Sins & Secrets: Raymond
programme.desc: In 1991, Raymond, Washington hairdresser Kathy Loreno left her family and friends behind without so much as a goodbye. Years later, investigators finally discovered the truth about her disappearance.

programme.title: Sins & Secrets: Topeka
programme.desc: In 2002 in Topeka, Kansas, newly engaged Michael Sisco and Karen Harkness were brutally shot from the foot of their bed while they slept.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Written in Blood
programme.desc: A community is shocked when Antoine McKenzie is brazenly shot outside an auto parts store in broad daylight. The only lead left for Lt. Joe Kenda is a final message written in the victim’s own blood.
